  <prompt>
    Fix RB-T028-03/04/05/06 — the HIGH-severity 4-entry cluster with shared root cause: endpoint metadata generation aborts at startup because `INotificationService` (and similar) is registered conditionally (inside a feature-flag `if` block, e.g., `if (Analysis:Enabled) services.AddNotificationService();`) but the corresponding endpoints map unconditionally (`MapKnowledgeBaseEndpoints` / `MapChatEndpoints` / `MapReAnalysisFlowEndpoints` / `MapAuthorizationEndpoints` are mapped regardless of the flag). ASP.NET Core's startup endpoint-metadata generation fails on the FIRST unresolvable handler, taking down the entire pipeline.

    Production fix: per-case decision per the ledger recommendation — either (a) make service registration unconditional for services whose endpoints map unconditionally, OR (b) make endpoint mapping conditional on the same flag. Choose per-case based on whether the flag is product-meaningful (e.g., a real kill switch) or just an internal feature-not-shipped guard. The ledger recommends "conditional endpoint mapping approach (option 1) consistently across all 4 affected endpoint families (KB, Chat, ReAnalysis, Auth)" per single PR.

    D-02 cluster exception applies: ONE production change closes all 4 ledger entries. Commit message MUST cite RB-T028-03, RB-T028-04, RB-T028-05, RB-T028-06 (NFR-04).

    37 tests flip Skip → Pass on success (13 KnowledgeBase + 11 Chat + 8 ReAnalysisFlow + 5 Auth).
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET developer with BFF DI + endpoint-registration discipline. ADR-010 (DI minimalism) + ADR-018 (kill switches) aware: the conditional-registration root cause is precisely the kind of application question those ADRs govern.</role>

  <goal>
    Seven deliverables verified:
    1. Single production fix applied across DI registration / endpoint mapping pair (either registration made unconditional, or endpoint mapping made conditional — per-case, ledger recommends option-1).
    2. Affected production files: typically `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/AiNotificationModule.cs` (or wherever `INotificationService` is registered) + endpoint definition files: `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/KnowledgeBaseEndpoints.cs`, `Api/Ai/ChatEndpoints.cs`, `Api/Ai/ReAnalysisFlowEndpoints.cs`, `Api/Authorization/AuthorizationEndpoints.cs` (or equivalent — VERIFY paths via Grep at task start).
    3. Test fixtures unchanged (NFR-01) — 4 fixtures continue to set `Analysis:Enabled=false`; production now boots cleanly under that flag.
    4. 37 tests flip Skip → Pass:
       - KnowledgeBaseIntegrationTests (13 — RB-T028-03)
       - ChatEndpointsTests (11 — RB-T028-04)
       - ReAnalysisFlowTests (8 — RB-T028-05)
       - AuthorizationIntegrationTests (5 — RB-T028-06)
       Per-test trait changes from `real-bug-pending-fix` to `repaired`.
    5. All 4 ledger entries (RB-T028-03/04/05/06) Status transitions to `repaired` with shared fix-commit SHA + cross-reference to r2 task 011.
    6. Build passes (`dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` 0 errors).
    7. Per-fix triple-run validation: 3 consecutive `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/` runs with Failed: 0 (per design.md §8 R2 risk mitigation "per-fix triple-run").
  </goal>

