  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism — service registration discipline; do NOT add unnecessary registrations; favor making registration unconditional ONLY when the service has zero-cost-when-feature-off behavior; otherwise make endpoint mapping conditional</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-018">Kill switches — feature-flag application is the root-cause question; understand whether `Analysis:Enabled` is a product-meaningful switch (must keep conditional) or an internal not-yet-shipped guard (can simplify)</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">Minimal API — endpoint registration patterns; if conditional, use `if (flag) app.MapXxxEndpoints();` wrapper</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-008">Endpoint filters — RB-T028-06 (Auth) requires care: Authorization endpoints don't directly require `INotificationService`, but share endpoint-metadata-generation surface — the fix to RB-T028-03/04/05 auto-resolves T028-06</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">r2: production code IS in scope; this is the canonical r2 cluster fix</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-02">Each production code change &lt;50% line replacement per file; if exceeded across the cluster, escalation via `escalations/rewrite-request-T-011-RB-T028-cluster.md`</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-04">Commit message MUST cite RB-T028-03 + RB-T028-04 + RB-T028-05 + RB-T028-06 + resolution mode (`repaired`) — D-02 cluster exception</constraint>
    <constraint source="D-02">One production fix can close multiple ledger entries when root cause shared — RB-T028-03/04/05/06 cluster qualifies</constraint>
    <constraint source="D-03">HIGH severity gets code-review + adr-check at Step 9.5; if the fix touches auth endpoints, security review also</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md § F">Test update obligation — satisfied implicitly by 37 Skip→Pass transitions; no new test files needed (tests are existing and now pass)</constraint>
    <constraint source="RB-T028-03/04/05/06 ledger entries">PRs modifying `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/` MUST add/update tests in `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/`. Endpoints that map unconditionally must have unconditional service registration (per RB-T028-03/04/05/06, codified in CLAUDE.md §10) — this fix is the canonical implementation of that rule</constraint>
  </constraints>

