  <context>
    <background>
      r1 task 027 (clean host boot discovery) and task 028 (cluster classification) surfaced this as a 4-entry cluster sharing one root cause: ASP.NET Core's endpoint-metadata generation aborts at startup when ANY mapped endpoint's parameter binding cannot be resolved. The 4 affected endpoint families (KnowledgeBase, Chat, ReAnalysisFlow, Authorization) all live in the same host. When tests set `Analysis:Enabled=false`, the AI services (e.g., `INotificationService`) are not registered — but the endpoints are still mapped. Startup fails with `notificationService | UNKNOWN` — and all 37 tests across the 4 fixtures fail identically. RB-T028-06 (Auth) is included because Auth endpoints share the metadata-generation surface — once the AI-endpoint binding gap is closed, Auth tests pass without separate edits.

      **Path corrections from Phase 0 task 001 (2026-06-01)**: The r1 ledger's cited file `Api/Ai/ReAnalysisFlowEndpoints.cs` DOES NOT EXIST as a standalone file in the current codebase. ReAnalysis flow routes through `Api/Ai/ChatEndpoints.cs` + `Program.cs`. This STRENGTHENS the cluster root-cause hypothesis: the fix target is `Program.cs` (where endpoints are mapped unconditionally) + the DI module(s) where AI services are conditionally registered. Step 1 must Grep to discover the actual conditional-registration sites — do NOT assume `Infrastructure/DI/AiNotificationModule.cs` exists at that exact path. Task 001's reproducibility doc (`baseline/20-entries-reproducibility-verification.md`) has full path-correction details for RB-T028-02, RB-T028-05, RB-T028-07 — read it during Step 1 context load.

      r1's D-02 codifies the cluster-exception rule: ONE production change can close multiple entries when root cause is shared. r1's lessons-learned reinforces: "cluster-level classification scales." This task IS the canonical Phase 1 cluster fix.

      Critical risk per design.md §8 R2: "RB-T028 root-cause fix breaks other endpoint registrations." Mitigation: per-fix triple-run + staged rollout (one endpoint family at a time if approach (a) chosen) + automated revert via PR revert if any post-merge regression. Per-fix triple-run is mandatory before PR merge.

      Decision point at task start: option (a) make service registration unconditional, OR option (b) make endpoint mapping conditional. Ledger recommends option (1) which corresponds to option (b) above — conditional endpoint mapping. Owner judgment per ADR-018: is `Analysis:Enabled` a product-meaningful kill switch (option-b correct) or an internal-only guard (option-a correct)? Cite the decision in the PR description.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="000" status="must-complete-first">Baseline must establish cluster's current state</dependency>
      <dependency task="001" status="must-complete-first">Reproducibility verification must confirm all 4 entries valid</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

