  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read all 4 ledger entries (RB-T028-03/04/05/06) end-to-end. **Also read** `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/baseline/20-entries-reproducibility-verification.md` for the 2026-06-01 path corrections. Grep for `INotificationService` registration site(s) in `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/`; identify the exact `if`-guarded registration line — note: do NOT assume `AiNotificationModule.cs` exists at that path; discover via Grep. Grep for `MapKnowledgeBaseEndpoints` / `MapChatEndpoints` / `MapAuthorizationEndpoints` registration site(s) in `Program.cs` or equivalent. **Note**: there is no `ReAnalysisFlowEndpoints.cs` separate file; ReAnalysis flow is in `ChatEndpoints.cs` + `Program.cs` — confirm via Grep.</step>
    <step order="2">Verify the 4 test fixtures: read `KnowledgeBaseTestFixture`, `ChatEndpointsTestFixture`, `ReAnalysisFlowTestFixture`, `AuthorizationTestFixture`; confirm each sets `Analysis:Enabled=false`. NO test changes — fixtures stay as-is per NFR-01.</step>
    <step order="3">Decision: option-a (registration unconditional) vs option-b (endpoint mapping conditional). Apply ADR-018 judgment: if `Analysis:Enabled` is product-meaningful (a real kill switch), choose option-b (mapping conditional — endpoints disappear when off); if it's internal not-yet-shipped guard, choose option-a (registration unconditional — kept always available). Ledger recommends option-b for consistency across all 4 endpoint families. Document the decision in `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/decisions/D-08-rb-t028-cluster-fix-approach.md`.</step>
    <step order="4">Apply the production fix per the chosen approach. If option-b: wrap each of the 4 endpoint map calls in `if (configuration.GetValue<bool>("Analysis:Enabled")) app.MapXxxEndpoints();`. If option-a: lift `services.AddNotificationService()` (and friends) out of the feature-flag `if` block. Single PR; cluster commit.</step>
    <step order="5">Build: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` — confirm 0 errors.</step>
    <step order="6">Remove Skip + update traits across the 4 test files: `KnowledgeBaseIntegrationTests.cs`, `ChatEndpointsTests.cs`, `ReAnalysisFlowTests.cs`, `AuthorizationIntegrationTests.cs`. Change per-test `[Trait("status","real-bug-pending-fix")]` to `[Trait("status","repaired")]`.</step>
    <step order="7">Run focused tests: `dotnet test --filter "FullyQualifiedName~KnowledgeBaseIntegrationTests"`; `--filter "...~ChatEndpointsTests"`; `--filter "...~ReAnalysisFlowTests"`; `--filter "...~AuthorizationIntegrationTests"`. Confirm all 37 tests pass.</step>
    <step order="8">Per-fix triple-run validation: `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --logger trx` 3 consecutive runs; confirm Failed: 0 across all 3. Capture 3 TRX files in `baseline/per-fix-triple-run-rb-t028-cluster-{date}.md`.</step>
    <step order="9">Run Step 9.5 quality gates: `code-review` + `adr-check` skills (per FULL rigor). The `adr-check` MUST validate ADR-010 + ADR-018 compliance for the chosen approach.</step>
    <step order="10">PR creation: cite RB-T028-03, RB-T028-04, RB-T028-05, RB-T028-06 + resolution mode `repaired` (4-entry cluster, D-02 exception) in commit message + PR title; PR description includes the chosen-approach decision (D-08) + per-fix triple-run TRX references.</step>
    <step order="11">After PR merge: update `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/real-bug-ledger.md` — transition all 4 entries Status to `repaired` with shared fix-commit SHA + date + cross-reference to r2 task 011.</step>
    <step order="12">Update `projects/sdap.bff.api-test-suite-repair-r2/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md` — mark 011 as ✅; update `current-task.md`.</step>
  </steps>

